<TITLE> AUB convocation postponed after protests </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 27 (bdnews24.com)The convocation ceremonies at Asian University Bangladesh on Monday were abandoned as students refused to accept diplomas from none other than president Zillur Rahman. The vice chancellor told bdnews24.com at 2:50pm that the convocation had been postponed. The students had expected the chancellor, president Rahman, at the function and they were naturally unhappy when they did not see him there, Abdulah Ahsan Sadeque added. Her told reporters that the president did not come to the convocation as he was ill. The students protested as the convocation kicked off after 12:30pm without the chancellor at the Bangabandhu International Conference Centre. Customarily, the president hands the students degrees. But he and the University Grants Commission chairman professor Nazrul Islam failed to be with the students as scheduled. The convocation began at 12:55pm, chaired by the vice-chancellor. The students began agitating, prompting the vice-chancellor to leave. They refused to accept their diplomas from anyone else but the president. Tofazzal Hossain, an MBA student, told reporters that they boycotted the convocation because they considered it meaningless to accept certificates from anyone else. Students Mahbub Alam and Rahima Khatun also said they would accept their certificates from the president alone. b
